{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0e41a489-bda7-40c0-a6cb-77a4057b66c8","content":"**No, you no longer need `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` on .NET 10.**\n\nIn .NET 10, `dotnet test` was rewritten to natively use Microsoft.Testing.Platform. That property was only needed in .NET 9 to opt in. You can safely remove it — keep `EnableMSTestRunner` as it still tells MSTest to produce an MTP-based executable.\n\nHere's the cleanup:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01KtmmrhojAWyS1Qak1UviBK","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Removing obsolete property"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01Vcj2zLNCTrUZxMSAGGvxq8","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-a16bda9d8690484b8dc9764c158d9fd6/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>","new_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-a16bda9d8690484b8dc9764c158d9fd6/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"9d5bfa0c-39bc-4a99-af2a-0f1a952991ff","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is on .NET 10 SDK (10.0.100) and wants to know about native MTP support. Let me provide accurate information.\n\nIn .NET 10, `dotnet test` has been rewritten to natively support Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). The key changes are:\n\n1. **`TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` is no longer needed** — In .NET 9 and earlier, you had to set `<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>` to opt into MTP via `dotnet test`. In .NET 10, `dotnet test` natively uses MTP, so this property is unnecessary.\n\n\n2. **`EnableMSTestRunner` is still required** — this property tells MSTest to generate an executable test app that leverages Microsoft.Testing.Platform.\n3. By default, .NET 10's `dotnet test` command runs with MTP, though the legacy VSTest runner is still available via the `--legacy` flag if needed.\n\nFor their project, they should keep `EnableMSTestRunner` set to `true` but can safely remove `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` since it's no longer necessary on .NET 10.","outputTokens":635,"requestId":"7C19:175BE3:2672595:2A8D11E:69F940D9"},"id":"7cf5ddf7-9cf1-475d-9b8c-b2604e90ad77","timestamp":"2026-05-05T00:59:15.731Z","parentId":"c118688e-a218-4db5-8005-8744dd8d61c3"}
